Interface Queue<E>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue

    public interface Queue<E>
    Interface for a queue: a collection of objects that are inserted according to the first-in first-out principle
    Author:
    Richard Bryann Chua Adapted from the book "Data Structures and Algorithms in Java" by Michael Goodrich and Robert Tamassia
